 The inhabitants of this area are      
 mainly farmers, the spoken word being 
 in the local dialect of West          
 Worcestershire. Apart from the        
 intonation and "broad" sound generally
 heard, there are also some words which
 are peculiar to this area such as - { 
{Nesh}(finicky or fussy) {Mawkin}      
 (scarecrow) {Quoit}(pigeon) {Scutch } 
 (weed) {Nurgery}(runt) {Cratch}(mobile
 hay manger) {Saft}(stupid) {Wodgen}   
 (clump of hay) {Mithering}(nagging) { 
{Yampi}(simple minded) {Mummy Ruffin}  
 (wren) {Mog}(calf) {Jakes}(gipsies) { 
{Snap}(lunch).
